nsecurity, and the region's collapsing hydro-ecology. This book shows how the effort to construct a regional water regime cannot be separated from the necessity to construct an ecologically sustainable internal water regime in each co-basin state, particularly in terms of ecological resources conservation and ecosystem services protection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFood supplyzAfrica. 0aRegional planningzNile River Watershed. 0aRiparian areasxPolitical aspectszAfrica. 0aWater-supplyxPolitical aspectszNile River Watershed. 0aWater-supplyzNile River WatershedxManagement. 4aArea Studies : African Studies. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Comparative Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Regional Planning.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147854740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791478547423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791478547/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles